        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> NPCs, Corpse, PC, etc information does not get passed on to the client outside of the current zone one is in.  Beastlord pets and Wizzy familiars do zone, but any information that changes the buff (10 hour limit on buff/warder/familiar) such as a buff would have to be redone which is the same as summoning a new pet.  If this information did get passed on three things would happen:</P><P>A) Lag would increase dramatically.<BR>B) There would be no zone line and no way to zone from danger.<BR>C) Anything that can currently not go across a zone, wouldn't have a<BR>   zone line/load point to keep them from going across.</P><P><a href="Http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61013">Infernall</a> <a href="Http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=42507">Cryptwalker</a><BR>Lvl 52<BR>Goody Nature Server</P><P><i>"Time is meaningless to one who lives an eternity."</i><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
